                            <comment id="55615" author="keith" created="Fri, 5 Apr 2013 16:50:24 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;User error. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="55613" author="keith" created="Fri, 5 Apr 2013 16:50:11 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Sorry moved a little fast yesterday. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;opreport --session-dir=(right spot) -l -p /lib/modules/`uname -r` &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Did the trick. &lt;/p&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="55580" author="green" created="Fri, 5 Apr 2013 05:24:01 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;we used to package lustre module rpms with debug symbols by default, but then this patch: &lt;a href=&quot;http://review.whamcloud.com/4491&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://review.whamcloud.com/4491&lt;/a&gt; suppsedly enabled creation of lustre debuginfo rpm that you need installed.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;As for the zfs - no idea.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="55578" author="bzzz" created="Fri, 5 Apr 2013 04:05:46 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;oprofile should be able to get symbol from regular modules (.ko). it seems oprofile couldn&apos;t find them.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
